										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p dir="auto">Indira Gandhi Hospital (IGH), Dwarka, Delhi under the Health &amp; Family Welfare Department, Government of NCT of Delhi, has released an official notification for the engagement of Junior Residents (MBBS) on a purely ad-hoc basis.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Important Dates</strong></span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Walk-in Interview Date: <strong>02 March 2026 (Monday)</strong></li>
<li>Reporting Time: 09:30 AM (Candidates reporting after 11:00 AM will not be considered)</li>
<li>Notification Release: February 2026</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Application Fee</strong></span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Nil</strong> (No fee for any category)</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Vacancy Details</span></strong></h3>
<p dir="auto"><span style="color: #ff9900;"><strong>Junior Resident (MBBS)</strong></span> &#8211; 25 Posts</p>
<p dir="auto">UR-09, OBC-11 and EWS-05</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Eligibility Criteria</strong></span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Educational Qualification</strong>: MBBS degree from a recognized university + Completion of one-year compulsory rotating internship (completed on or after 01 March 2024).</li>
<li><strong>Registration</strong>: Must be registered with Delhi Medical Council (DMC).</li>
<li><strong>Age Limit (as on 02-03-2026)</strong>: Maximum 30 years.
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Age relaxation: OBC – 3 years (up to 33 years), PwD – as per rules.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Experience</strong>: Not required (suitable for freshers who have completed internship).</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Emoluments</strong></span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Pay Scale: Level-10 (Rs. 56,100 &#8211; 1,77,500) + NPA and other allowances as per rules.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3><span style="color: #339966;"><strong style="font-size: inherit;">How to Apply</strong></span></h3>
<ol dir="auto">
<li>Download and read the official notification from the link below.</li>
<li>Prepare all original documents + self-attested photocopies:
<ul dir="auto">
<li>MBBS degree &amp; marksheets</li>
<li>Internship completion certificate</li>
<li>DMC registration certificate</li>
<li>Date of birth proof (10th certificate)</li>
<li>Category certificate (if applicable)</li>
<li>Recent passport-size photographs</li>
<li>Any other relevant documents</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Appear in person at the venue on <strong>02 March 2026 at 09:30 AM</strong>.</li>
<li>Venue: <strong>Indira Gandhi Hospital (IGH), Sector-9, Dwarka, New Delhi</strong> (Conference Hall / specified location as per notice).</li>
</ol>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Important Links</span></strong></h3>
<p dir="auto"><strong>Download Official Notification PDF &#8211; </strong><a href="https://health.delhi.gov.in/sites/default/files/Health/circulars-orders/wigh_19.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">Click here to download IGH Delhi Junior Resident Walk-in Interview Notification </a></p>
