										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p dir="auto">The Delhi Subordinate Services Selection Board (DSSSB) has released Advertisement No. 02/2026 on 25 February 2026, announcing a golden opportunity for government job seekers in Delhi. This recruitment drive aims to fill 216 vacancies for various Group B and Group C posts across multiple departments, autonomous bodies, and local bodies under the Government of NCT of Delhi.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Important Dates</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Opening Date for Online Applications</strong>: 27 February 2026 (from 12:00 Noon)</li>
<li><strong>Closing Date for Online Applications</strong>: 28 March 2026 (till 11:59 PM)</li>
<li><strong>Exam Date</strong>: To be announced later on the official website</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">No offline applications will be accepted—only online submissions through the portal will be considered.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Application Fee</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>General/OBC/EWS</strong>: As per DSSSB norms (usually ₹100, check detailed advt.)</li>
<li><strong>SC/ST/PwBD/Ex-Servicemen/Women</strong>: Exempted</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Vacancy Details</span></h3>
<p dir="auto">Here is the post-wise breakdown of vacancies (including category-wise distribution):</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Assistant Manager (Tourism)</strong> (Post Code 01/26) &#8211; Delhi Tourism &amp; Transportation Development Corporation Ltd. (Group B) &#8211; 6 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Assistant Manager (General)</strong> (02/26) &#8211; DTTDC (Group B) &#8211; 6 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Assistant Manager (Accounts)</strong> (03/26) &#8211; DTTDC (Group B) &#8211; 3 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Assistant Manager (Legal)</strong> (04/26) &#8211; DTTDC (Group B) &#8211; 1 Post</li>
<li><strong>Assistant Manager (Air Ticketing)</strong> (05/26) &#8211; DTTDC (Group B) &#8211; 1 Post</li>
<li><strong>Assistant Manager (Public Relation)</strong> (06/26) &#8211; DTTDC (Group B) &#8211; 1 Post</li>
<li><strong>Assistant Grade – I (IT)</strong> (07/26) &#8211; DTTDC (Group B) &#8211; 6 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Radiographer</strong> (08/26) &#8211; Health &amp; Family Welfare Department (Group C) &#8211; 96 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Optometrist</strong> (09/26) &#8211; Health &amp; Family Welfare Department (Group C) &#8211; 15 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Junior Radiographer</strong> (10/26) &#8211; New Delhi Municipal Council (Group C) &#8211; 10 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Meter &amp; Relay Tester Grade-II</strong> (11/26) &#8211; NDMC (Group C) &#8211; 34 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Reporter</strong> (12/26) &#8211; Legislative Assembly Secretariat (Group B) &#8211; 10 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Katib (Calligrapher)</strong> (13/26) &#8211; Urdu Academy (Group C) &#8211; 1 Post</li>
<li><strong>Patwari</strong> (14/26) &#8211; Delhi Urban Shelter Improvement Board (Group C) &#8211; 15 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Junior Law Officer</strong> (15/26) &#8211; Delhi Urban Shelter Improvement Board (Group B) &#8211; 1 Post</li>
<li><strong>Chemical Assistant</strong> (16/26) &#8211; Office of the Commissioner of Excise, Entertainment &amp; Luxury Tax (Group C) &#8211; 2 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Stenographer Grade – I</strong> (17/26) &#8211; Delhi Pollution Control Committee (Group B) &#8211; 3 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Junior Laboratory Assistant</strong> (18/26) &#8211; Delhi Pollution Control Committee (Group C) &#8211; 2 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Book Binder</strong> (19/26) &#8211; Department of Delhi Archives (Group C) &#8211; 2 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Assistant Microphotographist</strong> (20/26) &#8211; Department of Delhi Archives (Group C) &#8211; 1 Post</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto"><strong>Category-wise Total</strong>: UR &#8211; 124, OBC &#8211; 40, SC &#8211; 17, ST &#8211; 16, EWS &#8211; 19 (Including horizontal reservations: PwBD &#8211; 14, ESM &#8211; 5, MSP &#8211; 8)</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Age Limit (as on cutoff date)</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Varies by post (generally 18-30/35/40 years)</li>
<li>Relaxations: SC/ST &#8211; 5 years, OBC &#8211; 3 years, PwBD &#8211; 10 years (additional for reserved categories), Ex-Servicemen &#8211; as per rules</li>
<li>Departmental candidates: Up to 5 years for Group B, up to 40 years for Group C (with conditions)</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">Check the official notification for post-specific age limits.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Educational Qualification &amp; Experience</span></h3>
<p dir="auto">Qualifications vary by post. Examples:</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Radiographer</strong>: 10+2 with Science + Diploma in Radiography/Radiology (or equivalent)</li>
<li><strong>Assistant Manager posts</strong>: Graduate + relevant diploma/experience in tourism/PR/accounts/etc.</li>
<li><strong>Patwari</strong>: 10+2 or equivalent + knowledge of land records (or as specified)</li>
<li><strong>Reporter/Stenographer</strong>: Graduation + shorthand/typing speed + relevant experience</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">Full details including essential/desirable qualifications, experience, and pay scales (ranging from ₹18,000 to ₹1,51,100 approx., Pay Levels 4-7) are in the official PDF.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Selection Process</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Tier-1 Exam</strong> (Objective MCQs) or skill test (for some posts like Stenographer/Reporter)</li>
<li><strong>Document Verification</strong></li>
<li>Final merit based on exam scores + reservations</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">Exam pattern, syllabus, and admit card details will be updated on the website.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">How to Apply Online for DSSSB Recruitment 2026</span></h3>
<ol dir="auto">
<li>Visit <strong><a href="https://dsssbonline.nic.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">https://dsssbonline.nic.in/</a></strong></li>
<li>Register with basic details (if new user) or login</li>
<li>Fill the application form for Advt. No. 02/2026</li>
<li>Upload scanned photo, signature, and documents</li>
<li>Pay fee (if applicable)</li>
<li>Submit and take printout</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto">Apply early to avoid last-minute rush. Read the full advertisement carefully before applying.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Important Links</span></h3>
<p><strong>Download Advertisement</strong> &#8211; <a href="https://dsssb.delhi.gov.in/sites/default/files/DSSSB/circulars-orders/final_advt_02-2026_1.pdf">Click Here</a></p>
<p><strong>Official Website</strong> &#8211; <a href="https://dsssb.delhi.gov.in/dsssb-vacancies">Click Here</a></p>
