										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p dir="auto">The <strong>Goa Staff Selection Commission (GSSC)</strong> has released <strong>Advertisement No. 2 of Year 2026</strong> for filling up <strong>722 Group C vacancies</strong> through online applications. This recruitment covers posts like Police Constable, Forest Guard, Warden, Matron, and others, offering stable careers under the Government of Goa.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Important Dates</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Advertisement Date</strong>: 20 February 2026</li>
<li><strong>Starting Date for Online Applications</strong>: 20 February 2026</li>
<li><strong>Last Date for Online Applications</strong>: 13 March 2026</li>
<li><strong>Date of Examination</strong>: To be intimated later through the website and local dailies</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Application Fee</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>For Pay Level 1 to 3</strong>:
<ul dir="auto">
<li>UR/EWS/OBC: ₹200</li>
<li>SC/ST/PwD: ₹50</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>For Pay Level 4 and above</strong>:
<ul dir="auto">
<li>UR/EWS/OBC: ₹400</li>
<li>SC/ST/PwD: ₹100 Payment can be made online via Internet Banking, Debit Card, Credit Card, or UPI. No offline mode is available.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Vacancy Details </span></h3>
<p dir="auto">Total Posts: <strong>722</strong> Here is the post-wise breakdown (including category reservations where specified):</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Range Forest Officer</strong> (Forest Department): 13 posts</li>
<li><strong>Platoon Commander (Male)</strong> (Home Guards &amp; Civil Defence): 4 posts</li>
<li><strong>Round Forester</strong> (Forest Department): 23 posts</li>
<li><strong>Police Constable (Male/Female)</strong>: 360 posts (Male: 302, Female: 58)</li>
<li><strong>Police Constable (Armed Police)</strong>: 119 posts</li>
<li><strong>Police Constable Driver (Grade-III)</strong>: 111 posts</li>
<li><strong>Constable (Greaser)</strong>: 1 post</li>
<li><strong>Constable (Electrician)</strong>: 1 post</li>
<li><strong>Forest Guard</strong> (Forest Department): 9 posts</li>
<li><strong>Assistant Superintendent (Male)</strong> (Prisons): 4 posts</li>
<li><strong>Warden (Male)</strong> (Prisons): 60 posts</li>
<li><strong>Matron (Female)</strong> (Prisons): 10 posts</li>
<li><strong>Lascar (Male)</strong> (Sports &amp; Youth Affairs): 5 posts</li>
<li><strong>Escort (Female)</strong> (Woman &amp; Child Development): 2 posts</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">Reservations apply as per Goa Government rules, including for Ex-Servicemen, Meritorious Sportspersons, Ex-Agniveers, and others (specific sub-quotas mentioned in the notification).</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Age Limit (as on last date of application)</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Range Forest Officer, Platoon Commander (Male), Assistant Superintendent (Male), Lascar (Male), Escort (Female): Not exceeding <strong>45 years</strong></li>
<li>Round Forester, Forest Guard: Not exceeding <strong>35 years</strong></li>
<li>Police Constable (Male/Female), Police Constable (Armed Police): Not exceeding <strong>28 years</strong></li>
<li>Police Constable Driver (Grade-III): Not exceeding <strong>25 years</strong></li>
<li>Constable (Greaser/Electrician), Warden (Male), Matron (Female): Not exceeding <strong>30 years</strong></li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto"><strong>Relaxations</strong>:</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Government servants: Up to 5 years</li>
<li>SC/ST: 5 years</li>
<li>OBC: 3 years</li>
<li>PwD: 10 years (additional for SC/ST/OBC)</li>
<li>Ex-Servicemen, Home Guards, Ex-Agniveers, and specific service categories: As per rules (e.g., up to 5 years for certain Home Guards/Drivers)</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Educational Qualification </span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Range Forest Officer</strong>: Bachelor’s Degree in Science with at least two subjects from Mathematics, Physics, Chemistry, Botany, Zoology, Forestry, or Agriculture.</li>
<li><strong>Platoon Commander (Male)/Round Forester</strong>: Higher Secondary School Certificate (12th) or equivalent.</li>
<li><strong>Police Constable (Male/Female/Armed Police), Police Constable Driver, Forest Guard, Warden (Male), Matron (Female), Assistant Superintendent (Male), Lascar (Male), Escort (Female)</strong>: Secondary School Certificate (10th) or equivalent.</li>
<li><strong>Constable (Greaser)</strong>: 10th + ITI in Diesel Mechanic/Fitter with 2 years experience.</li>
<li><strong>Constable (Electrician)</strong>: 10th + ITI in Electrician with 2 years experience.</li>
<li><strong>Police Constable Driver (Grade-III)</strong>: 10th + Valid driving license for Heavy/Light vehicles + 2 years experience as driver.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">Knowledge of <strong>Konkani</strong> is mandatory for all posts (desirable: Marathi). Physical standards (height, chest, endurance tests) apply for many posts, especially police and forest roles.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">How to Apply</span></h3>
<ol dir="auto">
<li>Visit the official website: <strong><a href="https://gssc.goa.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">https://gssc.goa.gov.in</a></strong></li>
<li>Read the detailed instructions, notification, and syllabus available on the site.</li>
<li>Register and fill the online application form carefully.</li>
<li>Upload required documents (e.g., photo, signature, certificates for age, education, caste, residence, etc.).</li>
<li>Pay the application fee online.</li>
<li>Submit the form before 13 March 2026.</li>
<li>Take a printout of the submitted application for reference.</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto">Apply separately for each post/category if eligible for multiple. Cut-off date for eligibility (age, qualification, experience) is the last date of application.</p>
<hr />
