										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p dir="auto">The Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) has released the Central Armed Police Forces (ACs) Examination, 2026 notification for recruiting Assistant Commandants (Group A) in various CAPF forces. A total of 349 vacancies have been announced (tentative and subject to change). This is a prestigious opportunity for graduates to join forces like BSF, CRPF, CISF, ITBP, and SSB as Assistant Commandants.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Important Dates</span></strong></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Notification Release Date: 20 February 2026</li>
<li>Starting Date for Online Application: 20 February 2026</li>
<li>Last Date for Online Application: 12 March 2026 (till 18:00 hours)</li>
<li>Last Date for Fee Payment: 12 March 2026</li>
<li>Date of Written Examination: 19 July 2026
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Paper-I (General Ability and Intelligence): 10:00 AM to 12:00 Noon</li>
<li>Paper-II (General Studies, Essay and Comprehension): 2:00 PM to 5:00 PM</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>e-Admit Card Download: Last working day of the preceding week of the exam date</li>
<li>Physical Standards Tests (PST) / Physical Efficiency Tests (PET): After written exam result declaration</li>
<li>Interview / Personality Test: After qualifying PST/PET</li>
<li>Medical Standards Tests (MST): After Interview</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Application Fee</strong></span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>General / OBC / EWS (Male candidates): Rs. 200/-</li>
<li>SC / ST / All Female candidates: Nil (Exempted)</li>
<li>Payment Mode: Online through Net Banking, Credit/Debit Card, or UPI only (No other modes accepted; fee non-refundable)</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Vacancy Details</strong></span></h3>
<p dir="auto">Total Posts: <strong>349</strong> (Tentative, liable to alteration; 10% earmarked for Ex-servicemen)</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Border Security Force (BSF): 108</li>
<li>Central Reserve Police Force (CRPF): 106</li>
<li>Central Industrial Security Force (CISF): 70</li>
<li>Sashastra Seema Bal (SSB): 53</li>
<li>Indo-Tibetan Border Police (ITBP): 12</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">Post Name: Assistant Commandants (Group A) in Central Armed Police Forces Reservation: As per Government norms.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Age Limit (as on 01 August 2026)</strong></span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Minimum Age: 20 years (born not later than 01 August 2006)</li>
<li>Maximum Age: 25 years (born not earlier than 02 August 2001)</li>
<li>Age Relaxation:
<ul dir="auto">
<li>SC/ST: Up to 5 years</li>
<li>OBC: Up to 3 years</li>
<li>Civilian Central Government Servants / Ex-Servicemen: Up to 5 years (cumulative for reserved categories in service)</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">Date of birth must be as per Matriculation/Secondary School certificate; no changes allowed post-submission.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Educational Qualification</strong></span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Bachelor&#8217;s degree from a recognized University incorporated by an Act of Central/State Legislature, or equivalent institution under UGC Act, or deemed University.</li>
<li>Candidates appearing in final year exams of 2026 are eligible but must produce passing proof later.</li>
<li>Degrees from distance learning/part-time/correspondence not accepted.</li>
<li>Professional/technical qualifications recognized as equivalent by Government may be considered if from approved institutions.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">Nationality: Indian citizen (or subjects of Nepal/Bhutan with Government consent). Both Male and Female candidates are eligible.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>How to Apply</strong></span></h3>
<p dir="auto">Applications must be submitted online only at <a href="https://upsconline.nic.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">https://upsconline.nic.in</a>. Follow these steps:</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Visit the official UPSC website or upsconline.nic.in.</li>
<li>Complete registration (create account if needed, generate Universal Registration Number &#8211; URN).</li>
<li>Fill the Common Application Form (CAF) and Exam Specific Module.</li>
<li>Upload required documents: Recent passport-size photo (20-200 KB .jpg), signature (20-100 KB .jpg), live photo, Photo ID, DOB proof, educational certificates, category certificates (OBC/EWS valid dates apply), etc.</li>
<li>Pay the fee (if applicable) via online modes.</li>
<li>Select exam centre (first-apply-first-allot basis) and force preferences (BSF/CRPF/CISF/ITBP/SSB).</li>
<li>Review, submit, and take printout of the application.</li>
<li>Apply early to secure preferred exam city; no withdrawal allowed.</li>
<li>After written result, update additional details within 15 days if required.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Important Links</strong></span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Official Notification &amp; Details: <a href="https://thesarkarinaukri.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/UC26.pdf">https://thesarkarinaukri.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/UC26.pdf</a></li>
<li>Apply Online: <a href="https://upsconline.nic.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">https://upsconline.nic.in</a></li>
<li>UPSC Official Website: <a href="https://upsc.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">https://upsc.gov.in</a></li>
</ul>
