										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p dir="auto">Mahanadi Coalfields Limited (MCL) has officially released the detailed recruitment notification (Advertisement No. MCL/HQ/Recruitment/Statutory/2026/120 dated 21 February 2026) for various statutory, technical, and clerical posts. A total of 667 vacancies are being filled across mining supervisory, surveying, translation, and pathology technician roles.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Important Dates</strong></span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Notification Release Date: 21 February 2026</li>
<li>Online Application Start Date: 16 March 2026 (10:00 AM)</li>
<li>Last Date for Online Application: 06 April 2026 (11:50 PM)</li>
<li>Cut-off Date for Age &amp; Eligibility: 06 April 2026</li>
<li>Tentative Computer Based Test (CBT) Date: To be announced on the official website</li>
<li>Tentative Admit Card Download Date: To be announced</li>
<li>Tentative Result Declaration Date: To be announced</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Application Fee</strong></span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>General (UR) / OBC (Creamy Layer &amp; Non-Creamy Layer) / EWS: Rs. 1,000/- + GST Rs. 180/- = Rs. 1,180/- (Non-refundable)</li>
<li>SC / ST / PwBD / Ex-Servicemen / Female candidates / Employees of CIL &amp; Subsidiaries: Exempted (No fee)</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Vacancy Details</strong> </span></h3>
<p dir="auto">Total Posts: 667</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Jr. Overman T&amp;S Gr-C: 192 posts</li>
<li>Mining Sirdar T&amp;S Gr-C: 448 posts</li>
<li>Surveyor T&amp;S Gr-B: 24 posts</li>
<li>Translator (Tr.) OL Clerical Gr. III: 1 post (Backlog vacancy only)</li>
<li>Technician (Pathology) Tr. T&amp;S Gr-C: 2 posts (Backlog vacancies only)</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Age Limit</strong> (as on 06 April 2026)</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Minimum Age: 18 years</li>
<li>Maximum Age for UR/EWS: 30 years</li>
<li>Age Relaxation:
<ul dir="auto">
<li>OBC (Non-Creamy Layer – Central List): 3 years</li>
<li>SC/ST: 5 years</li>
<li>PwBD (for Translator &amp; Technician posts): 10 years (UR), 13 years (OBC-NCL), 15 years (SC/ST)</li>
<li>Ex-Servicemen: Length of service rendered in Defence + 3 years</li>
<li>Employees of CIL &amp; its Subsidiaries (Departmental candidates): No upper age limit</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Overall maximum age in any case should not exceed 56 years (except departmental candidates)</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Educational Qualification &amp; Essential Requirements</strong></span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Jr. Overman T&amp;S Gr-C: 3-year Diploma / Degree in Mining Engineering + Valid Overman’s Competency Certificate (Un-Restricted) issued by DGMS + Valid Gas Testing Certificate + Valid First Aid Certificate</li>
<li>Mining Sirdar T&amp;S Gr-C: Matriculation / Equivalent OR Diploma / Degree in Mining + Valid Mining Sirdarship Certificate (Un-Restricted) issued by DGMS + Valid Gas Testing Certificate + Valid First Aid Certificate</li>
<li>Surveyor T&amp;S Gr-B: Matriculation / Equivalent OR Diploma / Degree in Mining / Mine Surveying + Valid Surveyor’s Certificate (Un-Restricted) issued by DGMS</li>
<li>Translator (Tr.) OL Clerical Gr. III: Bachelor’s Degree (B.A. or equivalent) with Hindi and English as subjects (Government-recognized Diploma in Hindi Translation is desirable)</li>
<li>Technician (Pathology) Tr. T&amp;S Gr-C: Diploma in Medical Laboratory Technology / Pathology from a recognized institute</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">All technical competency certificates must be valid as per current Coal Mines Regulations, 2017.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Pay Scale</strong> (as per NCWA-XI)</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Jr. Overman, Mining Sirdar, Technician (Pathology): Rs. 47,330.25 per month</li>
<li>Surveyor: Rs. 51,103.12 per month</li>
<li>Translator: Rs. 41,966.51 per month Plus Dearness Allowance, House Rent Allowance, medical facilities and other allowances as per company rules.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>How to Apply</strong></span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Visit the official website: <a href="https://www.mahanadicoal.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">https://www.mahanadicoal.in</a></li>
<li>Go to CAREERS &gt; Recruitment section</li>
<li>Read the detailed instructions carefully and click “I Agree”</li>
<li>Register by providing Post Applied, Name, Mobile Number, Email ID</li>
<li>Receive User ID and Password via SMS / Email</li>
<li>Login and complete the application form</li>
<li>Upload scanned copies of recent photograph (not older than 3 weeks), signature, and all required certificates (JPG/JPEG/PDF format)</li>
<li>Preview the form, make corrections if needed, and submit</li>
<li>Pay the application fee online (if applicable)</li>
<li>Take a printout of the finally submitted application for future reference</li>
</ul>
