										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p dir="auto">Western Railway has released a centralized notification (No. RRC/WR/04/2025 Apprentice dated 18/02/2026) for the engagement of <strong>Act Apprentices</strong> under the Apprentices Act, 1961. This recruitment invites online applications for <strong>5,349 training slots</strong> in various designated trades across different Divisions and Workshops under Western Railway jurisdiction for the year 2025-26.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Important Dates</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Online Application Start Date</strong> — 21/02/2026 @ 11:00 hrs.</li>
<li><strong>Online Application Closing Date</strong> — 23/03/2026 @ 17:00 hrs.</li>
<li><strong>Age Calculation Date</strong> — As on 23/03/2026</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Application Fee</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>UR / OBC / EWS</strong> — ₹100/-</li>
<li><strong>SC / ST / PwBD / Women</strong> — No Fee</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Vacancy Details</span></h3>
<h4><span style="color: #ff9900;"><strong>Apprentices</strong></span></h4>
<p><strong>Total Posts</strong> — <strong>5349</strong></p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Educational Qualification</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Matriculation (10th)</strong>: Passed under 10+2 system with minimum <strong>50% aggregate marks</strong> from a recognized Board.</li>
<li><strong>Technical Qualification</strong>: Must possess ITI certificate in the relevant trade affiliated to <strong>NCVT</strong> (list includes Fitter, Welder, Electrician, Diesel Mechanic, Mechanic Motor Vehicle, Electronics Mechanic, etc.).</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Age Limit</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Minimum 15 years and maximum 24 years as on 23/03/2026.</li>
<li><strong>Age Relaxation</strong>:
<ul dir="auto">
<li>SC/ST: 5 years</li>
<li>OBC: 3 years</li>
<li>PwBD: 10 years</li>
<li>Ex-Servicemen: Additional relaxation (10 years + length of military service + 3 years), subject to conditions (min. 6 months continuous service in Defence; does not apply if already in civil Govt. job post-Ex-Servicemen status).</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Pay / Stipend</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Selected apprentices will undergo <strong>one-year training</strong>.</li>
<li>Stipend paid as per extant Railway Board rules and directives (typically based on Apprentices Act norms for ITI trades).</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">How to Apply</span></h3>
<ol dir="auto">
<li>Visit the official website: <a href="https://www.rrc-wr.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">https://www.rrc-wr.com</a></li>
<li>Read the full notification carefully and ensure eligibility.</li>
<li>Register and fill the online application form with personal details, trade, Aadhaar number, marks/CGPA, preferred Division/Workshop (only one choice allowed; final and binding).</li>
<li>Upload required scanned documents (SSC marksheet/certificate, ITI certificate/marks, caste/EWS/PwBD/Ex-Servicemen certificates if applicable, photo, signature).</li>
<li>Pay application fee online (if applicable).</li>
<li>Submit the form and download/print the application for reference.</li>
<li>No hard copies to be sent by post.</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto">Applicants must have a valid/active email ID and mobile number. Aadhaar number mandatory (or Enrolment ID if card not received).</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;">Important Links</span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Official Notification: <a href="https://www.rrc-wr.com/rrwc/Files/2683.pdf">https://www.rrc-wr.com/rrwc/Files/2683.pdf</a></li>
<li>Online Application:  <a href="https://www.rrc-wr.com/">https://www.rrc-wr.com/</a></li>
<li>Official Website: <a href="https://www.rrc-wr.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">https://www.rrc-wr.com</a></li>
</ul>
