										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p dir="auto">The Arunachal Pradesh Public Service Commission (APPSC) has released the official notification for Assistant Professor Examination-2026 (Advertisement No. 01/2026). Eligible candidates can join as Assistant Professors in various disciplines in Government Colleges under the Department of Education, Government of Arunachal Pradesh.</p>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Important Dates</span></strong></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Online Application Start Date</strong> — 23 January 2026 (from 1700 hours / 5:00 PM)</li>
<li><strong>Last Date for Online Application Submission</strong> — 23 February 2026 (before 1100 hours / 11:00 AM)</li>
<li><strong>Notification Release</strong> — January 2026</li>
<li>Interview dates to be notified later by APPSC.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Application Fee</strong></span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>APST Candidates</strong> — ₹150/-</li>
<li><strong>Other Candidates</strong> — ₹200/-</li>
<li><strong>PwBD Candidates</strong> — Exempted (as per Arunachal Pradesh Rights of Persons with Disabilities Rules, 2018)</li>
<li>Fee to be paid online during application submission.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Vacancy Details</strong></span></h3>
<p dir="auto"><span style="color: #ff9900;"><strong>Assistant Professor &#8211; </strong></span>(Group-&#8216;A&#8217; Gazetted Non-Ministerial)</p>
<p dir="auto"><strong>Total Posts</strong> — <strong>145</strong></p>
<p dir="auto"><strong>Subject-wise vacancy </strong></p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>English: 18</li>
<li>Hindi: 14</li>
<li>History: 21</li>
<li>Political Science: 18</li>
<li>Economics: 13</li>
<li>Geography: 13</li>
<li>Education: 9</li>
<li>Commerce: 6</li>
<li>Mathematics: 6</li>
<li>Zoology: 6</li>
<li>Botany: 5</li>
<li>Physics: 5</li>
<li>Chemistry: 7</li>
<li>Sociology: 2</li>
<li>Anthropology: 2</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Educational Qualification</strong> </span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Master&#8217;s degree with at least 55% marks (or equivalent grade) in the concerned/relevant/allied subject from an Indian University or accredited foreign university.</li>
<li>Relaxation of 5% marks (to 50%) for ST/SC candidates at Master&#8217;s and Bachelor&#8217;s levels.</li>
<li>Must have cleared UGC NET/CSIR NET or equivalent (SLET/SET), OR hold a Ph.D. degree as per UGC regulations (2009/2016 amendments).</li>
<li>Exemptions for Ph.D. holders (pre-2009 registrations under specific conditions; top-500 global university Ph.D.s exempt NET).</li>
<li>NET not required for subjects where UGC/CSIR does not conduct tests.</li>
<li>Academic score calculated per UGC Appendix-II (Table 3B) for shortlisting.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><span style="color: #339966;"><strong>Age Limit </strong></span></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Upper Age Limit: Up to 30 years (general).</li>
<li>Relaxation: 5 years for ST/SC candidates (up to 35 years).</li>
<li>For APST candidates: Up to 37 years (with further relaxations as applicable).</li>
<li>Additional concessions for PwBD and regular Arunachal Pradesh Government servants per rules.</li>
<li>As per &#8220;Assistant Professor for Government Colleges of Arunachal Pradesh&#8221; Recruitment Rules 2024.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Pay Scale / Salary</span></strong></h3>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Pay Matrix Level-10</strong> — Rs. 57,700 &#8211; 1,82,400/-</li>
<li>Group-&#8216;A&#8217; Gazetted (Non-Ministerial) post.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 dir="auto"><strong><span style="color: #339966;">How to Apply</span></strong></h3>
<ol dir="auto">
<li>Visit the official APPSC website: <a href="https://appsc.gov.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">https://appsc.gov.in/</a></li>
<li>Complete mandatory <strong>One Time Registration (OTR)</strong> if not already registered (existing users can login directly).</li>
<li>Go to the recruitment/advertisement section or &#8220;Apply&#8221; link for <strong>Assistant Professor Examination-2026</strong>.</li>
<li>Read the detailed advertisement carefully.</li>
<li>Fill the online application form with accurate details.</li>
<li>Upload scanned copies of required documents (photo, signature, Matriculation certificate for DOB, APST/ST/SC certificate, educational certificates, NET/Ph.D. proof, publications if applicable, PwBD certificate, PRC/Aadhaar, etc.).</li>
<li>Pay the application fee online (if applicable).</li>
<li>Submit the form before the deadline and take a printout for reference.</li>
