										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>The <strong>NHM Bilaspur Recruitment 2026</strong> (officially for contractual positions in the year 2025-26 under the <strong>National Health Mission</strong>, Chhattisgarh) is now open for applications. Issued by the <strong>Office of the Chief Medical and Health Officer (CMHO), District Bilaspur</strong>, this drive aims to fill essential support and multi-purpose roles in various health facilities, including Nutrition Rehabilitation Centres (NRC), Sick Newborn Care Units (SNCU), and general health services across the district.</p>



<p>This is a merit-based, contractual recruitment with <strong>no written exam</strong> — selection relies on qualifications, experience, and other criteria. It&#8217;s an excellent opportunity for local Chhattisgarh residents seeking stable <strong>government jobs in healthcare</strong> in Bilaspur.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">NHM Bilaspur Recruitment 2026 Overview</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Recruiting Authority</strong>: Chief Medical and Health Officer (CMHO), Bilaspur under National Health Mission (NHM), Chhattisgarh</li>



<li><strong>Total Vacancies</strong>: 146 Posts</li>



<li><strong>Nature of Posts</strong>: Purely contractual for the financial year 2025-26 (as approved in the district&#8217;s ROP)</li>



<li><strong>Application Mode</strong>: Online only</li>



<li><strong>Official Website</strong>: bilaspur.gov.in (notices section) | Application Portal: nhms.icccbilaspur.in/recruitment/apply/</li>



<li><strong>Advertisement Reference</strong>: Available as PDF on bilaspur.gov.in (file size ~277 KB)</li>



<li><strong>Application Period</strong>: Started <strong>February 14, 2026</strong> | Last Date <strong>February 28, 2026</strong> (up to midnight)</li>



<li><strong>Selection Process</strong>: Merit-based (educational qualifications, relevant experience, etc.); no test or interview mentioned. Merit list will be published on the official site, followed by claim/objection if applicable.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Detailed Post-wise Vacancies and Eligibility</h3>



<p>The recruitment covers various Class IV/support and field-level roles in health units. The official advertisement lists the posts with total vacancies (category-wise reservations like UR, SC, ST, OBC as per Chhattisgarh govt norms are detailed in the PDF table).</p>



<p>Key posts include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Attendant</strong> (in units like NRC, SNCU, general wards) — Significant vacancies (forms a major part of the 146 total)</li>



<li><strong>Multi-Purpose Worker (MPW)</strong> — Field/community health support roles</li>



<li><strong>Cook-NRC</strong> — For Nutrition Rehabilitation Centre kitchens</li>



<li><strong>Cleaner-SNCU</strong> — Cleaning and hygiene in Sick Newborn Care Units</li>



<li><strong>Aaya Bai-SNCU</strong> — Support staff (female attendant/helper) in SNCU</li>



<li><strong>House Keeping Staff</strong> — General facility maintenance and cleaning</li>



<li><strong>Other Equivalent Posts</strong> — Class IV support roles in various health programs/units</li>
</ul>



<p><strong>Note</strong>: Exact vacancy breakup per post (total + reserved categories) and any sub-variations are in the official PDF advertisement. Some related NHM drives in Bilaspur mention overlapping or separate posts (e.g., Pharmacist, ANM in other notifications), but this specific drive focuses on <strong>support and attendant-level positions</strong> totaling 146.</p>



<p><strong>Eligibility Criteria</strong> (General; post-specific details in official PDF):</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Educational Qualification</strong>:
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Attendant, Cleaner, Aaya Bai, House Keeping, Cook-NRC: <strong>8th Pass</strong> or <strong>10th Pass</strong> (as applicable for Class IV equivalent roles).</li>



<li>MPW: <strong>10th/12th Pass</strong> with relevant MPW training/certificate.</li>



<li>Other support roles: Minimum 8th/10th Pass; preference for relevant experience or training.</li>
</ul>
</li>



<li><strong>Age Limit</strong>: 18 to 64 years (calculated as on January 1, 2026, or relevant date; relaxations for SC/ST/OBC as per Chhattisgarh rules).</li>



<li><strong>Domicile</strong>: Preference for Chhattisgarh residents (local candidates prioritized).</li>



<li><strong>Experience</strong>: Relevant experience (if any) scored in merit; not mandatory for all entry-level posts.</li>



<li><strong>Other</strong>: Must meet NHM Chhattisgarh Human Resources Policy 2018 guidelines.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Salary / Remuneration</h3>



<p>Contractual pay as per NHM ROP 2025-26 norms (consolidated, monthly):</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Support roles (Attendant, Cleaner, Aaya Bai, House Keeping, Cook): Approximately <strong>₹10,000 – ₹18,000</strong> per month.</li>



<li>MPW and similar field roles: Approximately <strong>₹15,000 – ₹25,000</strong> per month (including allowances; exact amount per post specified in notification).</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How to Apply Online</h3>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Visit <strong>bilaspur.gov.in</strong> → Go to &#8220;Notices&#8221; or &#8220;Recruitment&#8221; section.</li>



<li>Locate the advertisement: &#8220;Advertisement for recruitment of employees on various posts in the year 2025-26 on contract basis under National Health Mission.&#8221;</li>



<li>Download the PDF for full post details, eligibility, vacancies, and instructions.</li>



<li>Click the application link: <strong><a href="https://nhms.icccbilaspur.in/recruitment/apply/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">https://nhms.icccbilaspur.in/recruitment/apply/</a></strong></li>



<li>Register with basic details, fill the form (personal info, qualifications, experience).</li>



<li>Upload scanned documents: Educational certificates, age proof, caste certificate (if applicable), experience proofs, photo, signature, etc.</li>



<li>Review and submit before <strong>February 28, 2026</strong>.</li>



<li>Take a printout of the application/confirmation.</li>
</ol>



<p><strong>Application Fee</strong>: Typically nil or very minimal (confirm in PDF; often exempted for such drives).</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Important Dates (2026)</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Online Application Start: February 14</li>



<li>Last Date for Submission: February 28 (midnight)</li>



<li>Merit List Publication &amp; Further Steps: To be updated on bilaspur.gov.in or application portal.</li>
</ul>



<p>This recruitment strengthens public health services in Bilaspur district under NHM. It&#8217;s a straightforward, no-exam opportunity for eligible candidates, especially 8th/10th pass locals.</p>



