										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>The <strong>Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI)</strong>, the apex regulator of the securities market, has announced an exciting opportunity for young talent through the <strong>SEBI Young Professional Recruitment 2026</strong>. This recruitment drive aims to engage <strong>91 Young Professionals</strong> across specialized domains on a contractual basis. It&#8217;s a golden chance for graduates, postgraduates, and professionals in finance, law, IT, and related fields to gain hands-on experience in India&#8217;s dynamic capital markets.</p>



<p>If you&#8217;re searching for &#8220;SEBI Recruitment 2026&#8221;, &#8220;SEBI Young Professional 91 Posts&#8221;, or &#8220;SEBI YP Recruitment 2026 apply online&#8221;, this comprehensive guide covers everything you need: notification details, vacancies, eligibility, salary, selection process, important dates, and step-by-step application guidance.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Why Join SEBI as a Young Professional in 2026?</h3>



<p>Working with SEBI offers unparalleled exposure to securities regulation, market operations, policy formulation, and investor protection. Selected candidates will contribute to real-world projects in Mumbai, build a strong foundation in financial markets, and earn a competitive monthly stipend of <strong>₹70,000</strong> (all-inclusive). This one-year program (extendable based on performance) is ideal for those eyeing careers in regulatory bodies, banking, finance, or compliance.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">SEBI Young Professional Recruitment 2026 Overview</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Organization</strong>: Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI)</li>



<li><strong>Post Name</strong>: Young Professional</li>



<li><strong>Total Vacancies</strong>: 91</li>



<li><strong>Nature of Engagement</strong>: Contractual (initially one year)</li>



<li><strong>Location</strong>: Mumbai</li>



<li><strong>Stipend</strong>: ₹70,000 per month (all-inclusive)</li>



<li><strong>Official Website</strong>: <a href="https://www.sebi.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">www.sebi.gov.in</a></li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Domain-Wise Vacancy Breakdown</h3>



<p>SEBI has distributed the <strong>91 posts</strong> across key domains to support its regulatory functions:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Securities Market Operations</strong>: 40 Posts</li>



<li><strong>Information Technology</strong>: 29 Posts</li>



<li><strong>Law</strong>: 13 Posts</li>



<li><strong>Rajbhasha</strong>: 5 Posts</li>



<li><strong>Research</strong>: 4 Posts</li>
</ul>



<p>These roles allow professionals to work in areas like market surveillance, legal compliance, IT systems for securities, policy research, and official language implementation.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Eligibility Criteria for SEBI Young Professional 2026</h3>



<p>Eligibility varies by domain, but common requirements include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Educational Qualification</strong>:
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Securities Market Operations: Post-graduate degree in relevant fields (Finance, Economics, Commerce, etc.) or professional qualifications like CA/CMA/CFA/CS.</li>



<li>Law: LLB/LLM or equivalent.</li>



<li>Information Technology: B.E./B.Tech/MCA/M.Sc in IT/Computer Science or related.</li>



<li>Research: Post-graduate in Economics/Finance/Statistics or similar.</li>



<li>Rajbhasha: Master&#8217;s in Hindi with English as a subject or equivalent.</li>
</ul>
</li>



<li><strong>Age Limit</strong>: Maximum 30 years (as of the notification date; relaxations apply for reserved categories as per SEBI rules).</li>



<li><strong>Experience</strong>: Freshers or candidates with relevant experience may apply, depending on the domain.</li>
</ul>



<p>Always refer to the official notification PDF on sebi.gov.in for stream-specific details.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Important Dates for SEBI Recruitment 2026</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Notification Release</strong>: February 2026</li>



<li><strong>Online Application Start Date</strong>: February 8/10, 2026 (varies slightly across sources; confirm on official site)</li>



<li><strong>Last Date to Apply Online</strong>: February 28, 2026 / March 2, 2026</li>



<li><strong>Selection Process Timeline</strong>: To be announced post-application closure</li>
</ul>



<p>Apply early to avoid last-minute technical issues!</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Selection Process</h3>



<p>The selection typically involves:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Screening</strong> of applications based on eligibility.</li>



<li><strong>Computer-Based Test (CBT)</strong> or domain-specific assessment (online mode).</li>



<li><strong>Interview</strong> for shortlisted candidates.</li>



<li><strong>Document Verification</strong>.</li>
</ol>



<p>Final merit will consider performance across stages.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Salary and Benefits</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Monthly Stipend</strong>: ₹70,000 (all-inclusive; no additional allowances mentioned).</li>



<li><strong>Duration</strong>: One-year contract, with potential extension based on performance and organizational needs.</li>



<li><strong>Other Perks</strong>: Exposure to high-level regulatory work, networking in finance sector, and resume-building experience.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How to Apply Online for SEBI Young Professional 2026</h3>



<p>Follow these steps:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Visit the official SEBI website: <a href="https://www.sebi.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">www.sebi.gov.in</a>.</li>



<li>Navigate to the &#8220;Careers&#8221; or &#8220;Vacancies&#8221; section.</li>



<li>Look for &#8220;SEBI Young Professional Program 2026&#8221; or similar link.</li>



<li>Register/login and fill the online application form.</li>



<li>Upload required documents (photo, signature, certificates).</li>



<li>Submit the form (no application fee in most cases).</li>



<li>Download/print the confirmation page.</li>
</ol>



<p><strong>Tip</strong>: Keep scanned copies of educational certificates, ID proof, and experience letters ready.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Preparation Tips for SEBI Young Professional Exam/Interview</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Focus on domain knowledge (e.g., securities laws, IT in finance, market regulations).</li>



<li>Stay updated on current affairs in Indian capital markets, SEBI regulations, and economic policies.</li>



<li>Practice aptitude, reasoning, and English for any screening test.</li>



<li>Review SEBI&#8217;s annual reports and key regulations on the official site.</li>
</ul>



<p>This recruitment is highly competitive, so thorough preparation is key.</p>



<p>Don&#8217;t miss this prestigious opportunity to kickstart your career with India&#8217;s premier securities regulator! Head to the official SEBI website now to check the detailed notification PDF and apply before the deadline closes.</p>



