										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>Central Electronics Limited (<strong>CEL Recruitment 2026</strong>) has released a major job notification for <strong>34 posts</strong> under Advertisement No. 118/Pers/1/2026. As a <strong>Mini Ratna</strong> Public Sector Undertaking (PSU) under the Department of Scientific &amp; Industrial Research (DSIR), Ministry of Science &amp; Technology, Government of India, CEL offers stable government jobs in areas like <strong>Solar Photovoltaic</strong>, <strong>Railway Signaling</strong>, <strong>Strategic Electronics</strong>, and <strong>Security &amp; Surveillance</strong>.</p>



<p>This is an excellent opportunity for engineering graduates, experienced professionals, and others seeking <strong>PSU jobs in 2026</strong>. Applications opened on February 10-11, 2026, and the last date to apply online is <strong>March 3, 2026</strong>. Don&#8217;t miss this chance for high-paying roles in a reputed organization!</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">CEL Recruitment 2026 Overview</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Organization</strong>: Central Electronics Limited (CEL)</li>



<li><strong>Advertisement No.</strong>: 118/Pers/1/2026</li>



<li><strong>Total Vacancies</strong>: 34 Posts</li>



<li><strong>Job Location</strong>: Primarily Ghaziabad, Uttar Pradesh (Sahibabad)</li>



<li><strong>Application Mode</strong>: Online</li>



<li><strong>Official Website</strong>: <a href="https://www.celindia.co.in/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">www.celindia.co.in</a></li>



<li><strong>Notification Release Date</strong>: February 10, 2026</li>



<li><strong>Online Application Start Date</strong>: February 10/11, 2026</li>



<li><strong>Last Date to Apply</strong>: March 3, 2026</li>



<li><strong>Selection Process</strong>: Varies by post (Written Test, Interview, Merit, etc.)</li>
</ul>



<p>CEL focuses on indigenous technologies and has a strong presence in defense, railways, and renewable energy sectors, making these roles highly desirable for career growth in government PSUs.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Vacancy Details and Posts</h3>



<p>The recruitment covers a mix of executive, trainee, and non-executive positions. Key posts include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Deputy General Manager (Electrical/Electronics, Microwave, etc.) – Senior leadership roles</li>



<li>Senior Technical Manager / Senior Manager</li>



<li>Deputy Engineer / Personnel Officer</li>



<li>Graduate Engineer Trainee (GET) – For fresh B.Tech/B.E. graduates (Electrical, Electronics, Mechanical, Computer Science, IT, etc.)</li>



<li>Management Trainee (MT) – For MBA/PGDM or relevant graduates</li>



<li>Clerk ‘C’ (NE5 Grade)</li>



<li>Operator ‘A’ (NE3 Grade)</li>



<li>Other contract-based roles like Hindi Officer/Rajbhasha Adhikari, Deputy Engineer on contract</li>
</ul>



<p>(Exact distribution across categories like UR, etc., is detailed in the official notification.)</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Eligibility Criteria</h3>



<p>Eligibility varies by post. Here&#8217;s a summary:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Educational Qualification</strong>:
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Graduate Engineer Trainee (GET): B.E./B.Tech in relevant branches (Electronics &amp; Communication, Electrical &amp; Electronics, Computer Science, IT, Mechanical, etc.) with minimum 55-60% marks.</li>



<li>Management Trainee (MT): MBA/PGDM or equivalent in relevant fields.</li>



<li>Deputy General Manager / Senior Manager: B.E./B.Tech + 16+ years experience in electronics, railway signaling, defense products, etc.</li>



<li>Clerk / Operator: 10th/Graduation or relevant qualifications.</li>



<li>Other posts: CA/ICWA, Any Graduate, etc.</li>
</ul>
</li>



<li><strong>Age Limit</strong> (as on January 31, 2026):
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>GET: Up to 27 years</li>



<li>MT: Up to 29 years</li>



<li>Deputy Engineer: Up to 33 years</li>



<li>Senior roles (DGM): Up to 48 years</li>



<li>Relaxations apply for SC/ST/OBC/PwD/Ex-Servicemen as per government norms.</li>
</ul>
</li>



<li><strong>Experience</strong>: Required for senior/executive posts (e.g., 16+ years for DGM).</li>
</ul>



<p>Check the official PDF for branch-wise details and preferences (e.g., experience in CENELEC standards, SIL-4 certification for railway roles).</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Salary and Benefits</h3>



<p>CEL offers attractive pay scales with perks typical of government PSUs:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Graduate Engineer Trainee (GET)</strong>: ₹40,000 p.m. (1st year), ₹45,000 p.m. (2nd year); Absorbed in E1 scale (₹40,000 &#8211; 3% &#8211; ₹1,40,000) post-training. CTC approx. ₹12-14 LPA.</li>



<li><strong>Deputy General Manager (E5)</strong>: ₹80,000 &#8211; 3% &#8211; ₹2,20,000; CTC ~₹23.87 LPA.</li>



<li><strong>Senior Manager (E4)</strong>: ₹70,000 &#8211; 3% &#8211; ₹2,00,000; CTC ~₹20.94 LPA.</li>



<li><strong>Clerk ‘C’ (NE5)</strong>: ₹20,000 &#8211; 3% &#8211; ₹65,000.</li>



<li><strong>Operator ‘A’ (NE3)</strong>: ₹17,500 &#8211; 3% &#8211; ₹50,000.</li>



<li>Contract roles: Consolidated pay (e.g., ₹60,000–₹75,000 p.m.).</li>
</ul>



<p>Benefits include DA, HRA, medical facilities, PF, gratuity, performance incentives, and more.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Application Process – How to Apply for CEL Recruitment 2026</h3>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Visit the official website: <strong><a href="https://www.celindia.co.in/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">https://www.celindia.co.in/</a></strong></li>



<li>Go to the <strong>Career Opportunity</strong> section.</li>



<li>Find the active advertisement (dated 10.02.2026).</li>



<li>Download the notification PDF for details.</li>



<li>Click on the online application link (if available) or follow instructions.</li>



<li>Fill the form, upload documents (photo, signature, certificates).</li>



<li>Pay the application fee (if applicable – check notification).</li>



<li>Submit and take a printout.</li>
</ol>



<p>Applications are online only. Visit regularly for updates.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Selection Process</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>For Trainees (GET/MT): Written test/interview + document verification.</li>



<li>For Executive/Senior Posts: Interview + experience evaluation.</li>



<li>Merit-based shortlisting for some roles.</li>



<li>Final merit list on the official website.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Why Apply for CEL Recruitment 2026?</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Prestigious Mini Ratna PSU with focus on Make in India technologies.</li>



<li>Opportunities in cutting-edge fields like solar, defense, and railways.</li>



<li>Job security, good salary, and career progression.</li>



<li>Ideal for freshers (via GET/MT) and experienced candidates.</li>
</ul>



